s! :-)\n=C2=A0\nCase 2: Eclipse/bo=\r\nndage exists and some acts increase it and some decrease it. It is not mere=\r\nly efforts to &quot;overcome&quot; this eclipse/bondage that may increase it. So many=\r\n other acts could increase it. Some people may have engaged in too many suc=\r\nh activities and accumulated so much eclipse/bondage/covering of the innate=\r\n divinity that it may actually need a lot of effort to undo it!\n=C2=A0\n*=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nIt is very easy to claim that all is god and that even c=\r\nonsidering that there is some covering is an ignorance.\n=C2=A0\nThough every=\r\nthing is Self, Self is that which is unborn and un-perishing. We are surrou=\r\nnded by many manifestations of Self that are transient, i.e. they are born =\r\nand they perish. When we come in contact with them, we do not focus on thei=\r\nr imperishable essence, but focus on the transient/perishable portion that =\r\nis more readily perceptible to our senses, manas, buddhi and chitta.\n=C2=A0=\r\n\nThis perishable/transient portion is what we mean by covering/eclipse.\n=C2=\r\n=A0\nSuppose one&#39;s leg is cut off, blood starts to gush out and one is about=\r\n to die in a little time. Can one remain equanimous during that time and ge=\r\nnuinely think &quot;this body and the blood I perceive are transient. They are a=\r\nctually manifestations of imperishable Self. I do not care about transient =\r\nmanifestations. I only care about the imperishable Self. I am Self&quot;?\n=C2=A0=\r\n\nThis is just one example. Depending on the person, many such examples can =\r\nbe given, where pretensions of &quot;I am Self&quot; can be shattered and one will be=\r\ng &quot;forget about Self. I am in deep trouble. Somebody please help me out of =\r\nthis situation&quot;!\n=C2=A0\nIf one is established in Self and NO situation ever=\r\n disturbs one&#39;s equanimity, only then one is realized. Such a state is not =\r\neasy to achieve as some pseudo-Vedantins may suggest.\n=C2=A0\nAs I said belo=\r\nw, this is just a case of &quot;a long path of\nconstant contemplation and self-c=\r\norrection can be reduced to a quick delusional\njump to the end&quot;. Unless one=\r\n catches it whenever something transient and perishable is drawing one&#39;s at=\r\ntention, one will not overcome each such instinct. Until each such instinct=\r\n is overcome, &quot;all is imperishable Self&quot; is just a theory one is repeating =\r\nlike a parrot. The covering/eclipse/bondage is quite real until then.\n=C2=\r\n=A0\n*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n=C2=A0\nUnfortunately, some assertions of Jnana Yoga an=\r\nd Adwaita Vedanta can be misleading. I will try to explain it with a nice a=\r\nnalogy from physics.\n=C2=A0\nThis world is made up of different objects. The=\r\ny are made up of molecules with a lot of vacuum in between them. Molecules =\r\nare made up of atoms and a lot of vacuum in between them. Atoms are made up=\r\n of electrons, protons etc and a lot of vacuum in between them. Even those =\r\nparticles are made up of smaller particles and a lot of vacuum in between t=\r\nhem. As you keep dividing, you will see that things are made up of subtle p=\r\nortions of matter and a lot of vacuum. When you go to the level of small pa=\r\nrticles, work by physicists such as Heisenberg, Broglie, Schroedinger etc s=\r\nays that you can&#39;t even observe and determine the properties of those parti=\r\ncles confidently without affecting them. They may not even exist as &quot;matter=\r\n&quot; with specific location and momentum or even as waves, independent of the =\r\nobserver.\n=C2=A0\nHowever, despite that &quot;quantum mechanics&quot; reality at the s=\r\nubtlest level, we have normal &quot;mechanics&quot; too. A lot of gross objects made =\r\nup of=C2=A0 those subtle particles are gross enough and obey some grosser l=\r\naws of physics (e.g. Newton&#39;s laws). We can find their positions, momentum =\r\netc accurately and make them move deterministically.\n=C2=A0\nWhen one is des=\r\nigning a car or a pulley system or a rocket, one can leave quantum mechanic=\r\ns and use normal mechanics. However, when one is doing research on bosons e=\r\ntc, one must pay attention to quantum mechanics. Otherwise, one will commit=\r\n errors.\n=C2=A0\nSimilarly, at the subtlest level, Self alone exists. Things=\r\n that seem to exist may not even exist independent of the observer. However=\r\n, there are also the laws of karma that govern the grosser reality (body, h=\r\nealth, job, spouse, children, house, car, money etc). Rishis taught Adwaita=\r\n Vedanta and also the laws that govern the world of duality (e.g. the law o=\r\nf karma).\n=C2=A0\nWhen one&#39;s awareness focuses on gross objects and one is w=\r\norking with the gross world, one better leave &quot;quantum spirituality&quot; (Adwai=\r\nta Vedanta) and focus on normal spirituality. However, when one&#39;s awareness=\r\n becomes very subtle and one starts to deal with mystical experiences, deit=\r\nies etc, one must pay attention to Adwaita Vedanta. Otherwise, one will com=\r\nmit errors!!\n=C2=A0\nBest regards,\nNarasimha\n--------\nAstrology & Spirituali=\r\nty Resources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n--------\n\n=C2=A0\n\n\n&gt;__________=\r\n______________________\n&gt; From: Kannan Iyengar &lt;prof.kannan.iyengar@...=\r\nm&gt;\n&gt;To: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com \n&gt;Sent: Saturday, August 24, 2013 5:21=\r\n PM\n&gt;Subject: RE: [vedic-wisdom] Re: which path to choose?-a dialog\n&gt; \n&gt;\n&gt;\n=\r\n&gt;=C2=A0 \n&gt;Dear Shri Narasimha Ji,\n&gt;Namasthe\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;1.=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 I deeply appreciate and feel grateful for having shared =\r\nyour\nunderstandings. I would kindly request you to permit me to share my un=\r\nderstandings\nwhich stand in definite contrast with that of your